comments: Corderships are c/12 diagonal spaceships built from switch engines. The trick in constructing a Cordership is to arrange the switch engines in such a way that they clean up each others' debris.
Middle: Two 6-engine constructions and a symmetric 8-engine.
Back: The classic 7-engine Cordership, shown with classic rear-end glider collisions.
All five of these Corderships were constructed by Dean Hickerson, who named them after the discoverer of the switch engine, Charles Corderman.
